OUT! TAKEN! Another good bit of catching and down goes the seventh wicket for New Zealand! Ravichandran Ashwin tosses it up again, on off stump. The ball turns in and Tom Blundell doesn't really come forward as he looks to push it out. Blundell gets an inside edge, back onto the pads and towards backward short leg. Cheteshwar Pujara takes a good low catch to his right and Tom Blundell's short resistance comes to an end.
Howout: c Cheteshwar Pujara b Ravichandran Ashwin

Commentary: On middle and flicked away onto the leg side.

OUT! CAUGHT! Ravichandran Ashwin is in a hurry to clean up the New Zealand tail now. Ashwin loops it up, around the off pole and allows the pitch to do the rest. The ball spins in as Tim Southee looks to press forward and poke at it. The ball goes off the inside edge, onto the pads and loops up towards short leg. The substitute fielder, Suryakumar Yadav dives forward and takes a good catch. William Somerville walks in at number 10 for New Zealand.
Howout: c sub Suryakumar Yadav b Ravichandran Ashwin

Commentary: On off, blocked.
Angled into the pads, this is worked through mid-wicket for one.
On off, blocked.
On middle and leg, pushed towards mid on.
Tossed up, on middle and kept out by William Somerville.
Flatter one, on off and kept out on the off side.
Uppish but safe! Tossed up, on off. Kyle Jamieson chips it towards mid off for a single.
Flighted ball, on middle and Somerville keeps it out.
William Somerville comes down the track but gets completely beaten in flight. This is on off and turns in, Somerville looks to work it on the on side but the ball goes off the pads onto the off side.
On off, Somerville presses forward and pushes it out on the off side.
On middle and leg, worked on the leg side.
Flighted ball, on off and spinning it yet again. William Somerville gets forward and pads it straight to short leg who pouches it.
Flatter on off. Kyle Jamieson gets forward and defends it to the off side.

FOUR! Short ball and punished! Shorter length outside off. Kyle Jamieson goes deep in his crease and punches it through covers for a boundary. Good effort by Mohammed Siraj there but the ball crosses the ropes.
Flatter and quicker on off. Defended off the front foot.
Slightly slower in air on off. Kyle Jamieson gets forward and defends it.
Shorter length, on off. Punched off the back foot towards the off side.
Tossed up on off. Kyle Jamieson gets forward and looks to defend.The ball kisses the outside edge of his blade and goes towards short third man.
Shorter length outside off. William Somerville looks to cut but misses.

NOT OUT! Great take from Wriddhiman Saha but William Somerville survives! On middle and leg, spins way down the leg side. William Somerville charges down the track but gets beaten in flight. He though quickly scampers back into the crease. Saha dives to his left and in one smooth motion, pouches the ball and whips off the bails. The replays show that the bat was grounded.
On middle, defended.
Shorter and on off, this is pushed to covers.
NO BALL! Once again a short leg fielder is hit but he seems okay now! A full toss on middle, William Somerville pulls it hard but it hits Iyer at short leg. He seems fine though.
Comes down the track and works it to mid on.
Tosses it up on off, it is pushed to mid off.
Flatter delivery on off. Kyle Jamieson blocks it off the back foot.
Flatter and shorter on off. Kyle Jamieson punches it to covers.
Flatter on off again. Kyle Jamieson gets his pads across and leaves it alone.
Another quicker delivery on off. Kyle Jamieson defends it with straight bat off the front foot.
On off and fuller. Defended off the front foot towards silly point.
Flatter and angling into middle and leg. Kyle Jamieson presses forward to defend it.
Shorter length around off. Punched towards the cover region.
Slower in the air on middle. William Somerville defends this off the front foot.
Nicely tossed up on middle again. William Somerville defends this off the inner half of his blade to short leg.
Flatter and quicker outside off this time. William Somerville looks to cut but misses.
Tossed up on middle. Turned away to mid-wicket.
Nicely tossed up on middle again, William Somerville blocks it out.
Axar Patel darts this quicker on off and middle. Kyle Jamieson blocks this off the back foot.
Fuller and flatter again on middle. Kyle Jamieson pushes it to mid on.
Quicker and flatter on middle. Kyle Jamieson gets forward and defends it again solidly.
Ohh.. extra bounce there! Slower in the air on middle. The ball bounces a little as Kyle Jamieson looks to defend it. He gets an inside edge onto his pads towards mid on for a single.
Tossed up on middle. William Somerville blocks it out to short leg.
Flatter and quicker outside off. William Somerville looks to push at it but the ball misses the outside edge of his blade.
Turning too much. On middle and leg, Kyle Jamieson looks to nudge it on the on side but misses and gets rapped on the pads.
Flatter one, on off and spinning in. Kyle Jamieson rocks back and keeps it down on the leg side.
Tossed up, on middle and this is flicked away through mid-wicket for a single.
William Somerville dances down the track and manages to keep it down towards short leg.

OUT! The resistance of William Somerville comes to an end! It was a gritty 26 ball duck for William Somerville but he has to depart now. Ravichandran Ashwin tosses it up, on off and Somerville looks to clear mid on. He though ends up chipping it straight towards Mohammed Siraj at mid on and the catch is taken. Ashwin gets his fourth now and just one wicket remains for the visitors.
Howout: c Mohammed Siraj b Ravichandran Ashwin

Commentary: Quicker but spraying down the leg side. Ajaz Patel looks to get a bat on that one but the ball is way down the leg side.

OUT! CAUGHT! It's all over! New Zealand have been bundled out for 62. Their lowest ever total against India! Axar Patel bowls this slower in the air on off. Kyle Jamieson looks to hit it away but the ball catches the outside edge of his blade and goes to Wriddhiman Saha behind the stumps. The ball hits him and loops in the air towards the off side. Shreyas Iyer at silly point dives to his left and takes a fantastic catch. The umpire gives that out but Kyle Jamieson reviews. The replays roll in and UltraEdge shows a spike as the ball passes his blade and Kyle Jamieson has to walk back.
Howout: c Shreyas Iyer b Axar Patel

Commentary: Southee starts off with a length ball, just outside off. Mayank Agarwal leaves it alone.
Pitched slightly further and outside off, Agarwal looks to drive but gets beaten.
On off and driven down towards mid off.
Wobble seam delivery, around off and jagging back in. Mayank Agarwal keeps it out.
A length ball, on top of off and Agarwal stays solid in defense.
FOUR! Just angled down the leg side and Mayank Agarwal is underway. On the pads, tickled away fine and into the fine leg fence.
FOUR! Easy pickings! Shorter ball, down the leg side. Pujara works it to the fine leg fence.
Shorter ball, around off. Pushed to covers.
Full and on middle. Pujara gets the inside edge past short leg.
FOUR! Punished! Short ball, outside off. Pujara rocks back and cuts it past point for a boundary.
Loopy ball, on off. Blocked out.
Full ball, on middle. Pujara blocks it off the front foot.
Full and on the pads. Agarwal looks to flick it away but gets the leading edge back towards the bowler.
Short ball, around off. Agarwal sways away from the ball.
Full and on off. Agarwal blocks it back to the bowler.
Short of a length, outside off. Mayank Agarwal lets the keeper collect it.
Short of a length, on off. Blocked out.
Length ball, on the pads. Mayank Agarwal works it past mid-wicket for an easy single.
Loopy ball, on off. Agarwal gets forward and blocks it.
Nice and full, on middle. Blocked off the front foot.
Loopy ball, on middle and leg. Mayank Agarwal gets forward to block it.
Darted on the pads. Agarwal looks to block but gets hit on the pads. There is an half-hearted appeal for LBW but not given.
Loopy ball, right on the off pole. Punched to point.
Loopy ball, on off. Blocked off the front foot by Mayank again.
Length ball, on the pads. Pujara flicks it to deep square leg for a couple of runs.
Length ball, on off. Blocked out by Pujara.
Short ball, on the body. Pujara nicely pulls it to fine leg for one.
Back of a length, right on off. Mayank Agarwal stays in the crease and blocks it.
Full ball, on off. Pushed to mid off.
Full ball, on middle. Blocked out.
Flatter ball, on off. Blocked out.
Loopy ball, on off. Pujara blocks it out.
Nice and slow, just outside off. Pujara puts in a stride to block it.
FOUR! Excellent shot! Pujara gets to the pitch of the ball and drives it past the diving cover fielder for a boundary.
Full and on the pads. Blocked out.
Shorter, on middle and leg. Pujara taps it to short leg.
Full and on off. Mayank puts in a stride and pushes it to mid off.
Short of a length, around off. Punched to point.
Full and on the pads. Mayank pushes it to mid on.
Overpitched delivery, around off. Mayank Agarwal drives it crisply to mid off.
Length ball, on middle. Mayank Agarwal gets his bat down in time to block it.
FOUR! Beautiful stroke! Length ball, around off. Mayank Agarwal drives it well. The man at mid off gets to his left and dives over the ball. Boundary.
Loopy ball, on off. Blocked out.
Full and on the pads. Pujara blocks it off the front foot.
Down the leg side. Worked past short leg for one.
A touch short, on off. Mayank Agarwal taps it to point.
Loopy ball, on leg. Blocked out with ease.
TOUGH CHANCE! Tossed up, on off. Agarwal gets down the track and hammers it straight back to Patel. He leaps up and gets his hands to it but it doesn't stick. The ball goes to long off for one.
Short ball, on middle. Pulled away to deep mid-wicket for one.
Full ball, on middle. Pushed back to the bowler.
Fuller ball, just outside off. Pujara gets forward to block it.
Short of a length, outside off. Left alone.
Short ball, on off. Pulled to deep square leg for one.
Length ball, on off. Blocked out.
Loopy ball, on off. Pujara gets the outside edge to third man for one.
Full and on off. Blocked out.
Darted on the pads. Mayank Agarwal works it to short leg.
Loopy ball, on off. Mayank Agarwal gets forward, lets the ball turn a bit and blocks it.
Flatter ball, around off. Pushed past cover for one.
Loopy ball, on middle. Blocked away by Pujara.
Starts with a short ball, on middle. Mayank Agarwal goes back and blocks it awkwarldly.
Length ball, on the pads. Tucked to the leg side.
Short of a length, on off. Blocked out.
Kyle Jamieson serves a length ball, on off. Mayank Agarwal stays in the crease to block it out.
Fuller ball, on off. Blocked out.
Lands outside off and comes back in. Mayank Agarwal covers the stumps and leaves it.
Tossed up, on middle and leg. Cheteshwar Pujara steps out of the crease and pushes it back to the bowler.
On the pads, nudged down towards fine leg for a single.
Flighted ball, on off and kept out by Agarwal.
Floated up, around off and stroked towards covers. The fielder over there misfields and they get a single.
Slowed up, around the leg stump. Cheteshwar Pujara looks to dab it down on the leg side but pads it straight to short leg.
SIX! Dragged down, on middle. Cheteshwar Pujara uses the crease well as he goes deep inside the crease and lifts it all the way, over the mid-wicket fence.
Short ball, on off stump. Mayank Agarwal gets right behind the line of the ball to block it.
Short again, outside off and Agarwal sways away from it.
Good-length ball, outside off. Agarwal opens the face of the bat and plays it through cover-point for a run.
Banged into the pitch, over middle. Pujara ducks under it.
Quick bumper, well down the leg side and left alone.
Another short delivery to end the over. On middle and Pujara ducks under it.
FOUR! Tossed up, around off. Mayank Agarwal dances down the track and hits it inside out, with the turn and over extra cover for a boundaryy.
Drifted into middle and leg, the ball spins away after pitching. Agarwal edges it down towards backward point for a single.
On middle, defended out.
This one turns square! Looped up, around the leg stump and the grips and turns away sharply. The ball keeps a bit low as well but Pujara manages to work it behind square on the leg side for one.
On off, Agarwal uses his feet to get it down towards long off for a run.

Flatter one, on off and this one goes on with the arm. Pujara pushes at it but misses and gets rapped on the pads. A stifled appeal but not given. Was there an inside edge on it? The replays show that there wasn't and had they reviewed, it would have been out.
Banged into the pitch, around off and Agarwal ducks under it.
On a length, around leg stump. Agarwal dabs it down towards short mid-wicket.
Another short one, at the body. Mayank Agarwal hops back to defend but the ball pops up off the handle and lands safely around point.
FOUR! Mayank Agarwal was ready for the short ball and takes full advantage of it. Short one, on off and this is pulled away in front of square for a boundary.
Fiesty bouncer, on leg stump and this one keeps on going down with the angle.
Back of a length, around off and Agarwal gets right behind the line of the ball to block it.
Tossed up, on middle and kept out towards short leg.
Slightly quicker, on the pads and Pujara dabs it down to the right of short leg.
On middle and leg, pushed out towards mid on.
Quicker one, fuller and on off. Pujara keeps it out on the off side.
On middle and leg, Cheteshwar Pujara uses his feet to get to the pitch of the ball and ease it down towards long off for a single.
On off, Agarwal stays solid in defense.
Shortish ball, angled down the leg side. Pujara ducks under it.
Another bouncer, pitching around off and going over middle stump. Pujara ducks under it yet again.
Kyle Jamieson comes from around the wicket and angles a short ball, across the body. Cheteshwar Pujara manages to keep it down towards the gully region.
Just short! Almost an action replay of the previous delivery. This time Pujara opens the face of the bat and looks to guide it but almost ends up giving a simple catch to gully.
A bouncer, down the leg side. Pujara sways away from it this time.

TWO LEG BYES! Streaky this time from Cheteshwar Pujara. A length ball, on the hips. Pujara looks to flick but the ball comes off the thigh pads and loops up between the keeper and the leg slip. The ball goes towards fine leg but Ajaz Patel cuts it off nicely and keeps it down to two.
On leg stump, flicked onto the leg side for one.
A skidder, on off stump and edged down towards slip.
On middle and leg, turned onto the leg side by Pujara.
Tossed up, on a length, around middle and leg. This one seems to be going down the leg side as Pujara misses the flick and gets rapped on the pads.
Tossed up, on off. Pujara comes forward and drives it down to long off for one.
Flighted ball, on off. Mayank Agarwal dances down the track and drills it to long off for a single.
Flatter delivery, well outside off. Agarwal keeps it out with ease.
Slowed up, on off and turning in. Agarwal awkwardly fends it off towards backward square leg.
On middle and leg, flicked onto the leg side.
Shortish ball, on the pads. Mayank Agarwal goes on the back foot to keep it down on the leg side.
On the pads, dabbed down towards short fine leg for a quick single. Patel has a shy at the bowler's end but misses and they get an overthrow as well.
On off, eased down to long off for one by Agarwal.
Quicker one, on off and pushed towards cover.
FOUR! Bowled on a driving length, outside off. Agarwal has a push at it but gets an outside edge down towards the third man fence for a boundary.
Tossed up, around off and spinning away. Left alone by Agarwal.
On middle and leg, pushed back towards the bowler.
Flatter one, on off and defended off the back foot.
Slightly fuller, outside off and Mayank Agarwal makes a leave.
On the pads, nudged down towards mid-wicket for a quick single by Pujara.
Dragged down, down the leg side as well. Mayank Agarwal rocks back to pull it away but misses.
Slightly shorter, on middle. Agarwal defends it off the back foot.
FOUR! Tossed up, on off. Mayank Agarwal skips down the track and crunches it back over the bowler's head for a boundary.
Pushed through on off stump and turning in, Agarwal works it off the back foot towards square leg for one.
On off and kept out by Pujara.
Uppish but safe! Tossed up, around middle and inviting the drive. Mayank Agarwal goes for it but hits it just wide of short cover.
On middle, pushed back to the bowler.
On off and punched down towards long off for a single.
Slowed up, on a length and outside off. The ball turns away as Pujara taps it to cover-point.
FOUR! Positive intent from the get go from Cheteshwar Pujara. Flighted, on middle and leg, Pujara comes down the track and clips it through mid-wicket for a boundary.
FOUR! And again! Very full, around the pads and Pujara works it through the huge gap at mid-wicket and picks up another boundary.

Just short! Southee starts off with a length ball, around off stump. Mayank Agarwal doesn't move his feet as he gets squared up. The ball goes off the outside edge and falls short to the right of Ross Taylor at second slip, who does manage to get a hand to it.
Angled into middle and leg, nudged towards mid-wicket.
Slightly fuller, on off and kept out on the off side.
FOUR! Southee strays onto the pads and gets punished. Fullish ball, down the leg side and Agarwal flicks it away into the fine leg fence.
Pitched up, on off and angling in. Agarwal leans forward and drives it nicely towards mid off.
Length again, on off and defended out by Agarwal.
Floated up, on middle. Cheteshwar Pujara strides forward to defend.
Tossed up, around off and spinning away. Pujara shows a pad at it but the ball goes through to the keeper.
FOUR! Shorter in length, on off. Cheteshwar Pujara uses the depth of the crease well and lifts it over mid-wicket and collects yet another boundary. Ajaz Patel being put under pressure here.
Tossed up, on off. Pujara skips down the track and pushes it to mid off.
Very full, on middle and pushed towards mid off.
Slowed up, around middle and leg. Pujara nudges it on the leg side.
A good bouncer, over off stump. Mayank Agarwal sways his head away from it.
Pitched up, well outside off and left alone by Agarwal.

NOT OUT! Excellent review from Mayank Agarwal and he knew that he hit it. A length ball, on middle and slanting in sharply. Agarwal looks to tuck it away but gets rapped on the pads. The visitors appeal and the finger is raised. Agarwal reviews and UltraEdge confirms that there was bat involved. Mayank Agarwal survives and Tim Southee is left a little frustrated.
Full, on off and blocked out.

A well-directed bouncer from Tim Southee, right around the helmet. Mayank Agarwal looks to hook but is not in control of the shot as the ball goes aerially behind square on the leg side. The fielder from deep square leg runs around to cut it off and keeps it to three.
On top of off, defended out by Pujara.
SIX! Yet another half-century for Mayank Agarwal. He's just growing in confidence now. Tossed up, around off and Agarwal skips down the track to lift it well over the extra cover fence for a biggie.
FOUR! Pushed through quicker, on off. Mayank Agarwal thrashes it uppishly through the cover region for another boundary.
Patel gives it a bit more air and drifts it into middle and leg. Agarwal strides out to defend.
Flatter delivery, on middle. Agarwal defends it off the back foot.
Around off and nudged away towards point.
Flighted delivery, on off and blocked out with ease by Agarwal.
A bumper from around the wicket and this one is over the leg stump. Cheteshwar Pujara ducks down and let's it through.

That seemed a bit nasty! Another bouncer, around leg stump and angled towards the body. Pujara sways away from it and thankfully gets hit on the arm guard, otherwise, the ball would have crashed right into the elbow.
Back of a length, down the leg side and left alone.
Another short ball, at the body. Cheteshwar Pujara hops to sway away from it but gets hit on the back this time.
Shorter in length, on leg stump and angling across. This time Pujara hops and defends it well.
Another short ball to end the over. Angled towards the body from around the leg stump and Pujara ducks under it. A maiden over for Tim Southee.
Drifting onto middle stump. Agarwal gets an inside edge onto the pads as he looks to defend.
On a length, on off and punched towards long off for an easy single. The 100 is up for India.
On the pads, kept out towards short leg.
Quicker one, outside off stump and going on with the arm. Cheteshwar Pujara pads it away.
Beaten! Nicely tossed up, on off and turning away sharply. Cheteshwar Pujara looks to block it but the ball goes past the outside edge.
Back-to-back maidens for New Zealand. On middle and defended out.

Short and on the body, Agarwal at first wanted to move out of the way. He then realised he's too late for it and ends up mistiming his pull on the leg side. It actually came off the glove and Agarwal is in pain.
On the body, Agarwal hops and blocks.
Yet another short one on the body, it is nudged on the leg side for one.
Yet another short one, Pujara lets it go over him.
Another one which is banged short. Left alone.
Outside off, shorter, left alone.
On middle, blocked.
Another one which is on the stumps, defended.
Angled into the pads, skids through, Agarwal goes back and blocks.
Slower through the air and on middle, defended with a big stride forward.

PUT DOWN! That had to stick. It came back like a rocket. Agarwal steps out and makes it into a half volley. He drills it back towards the bowler who sticks his right hand out but the ball bursts through and rolls towards mid on.
Slows it up and lands it on off, Agarwal plays it to covers.
Short and on the body, this is nudged to mid-wicket.
Extra effort on this delivery. It is on the body, extra bounce. Pujara does well to play it by taking a hand off the handle.
Another short delivery around middle and leg. Cheteshwar Pujara sways away from the line of the ball.
Another short one, does not quite bounce a lot. Blocked.
This time it is down the leg side. Left alone.
Two to end the over. This time he goes full and on middle, it is clipped through mid-wicket for two.
FOUR! Glorious! He is a top player of spin. Lovely use of the feet, makes room and lifts it over covers for a boundary.

OUT! TAKEN! Agarwal holes out! 11th wicket in the game for Ajaz Patel and New Zealand finally manage to get a breakthrough. It is tossed up. Agarwal comes down the track again and looks to go over long off this time. The ball though just turns a bit and hence, it is more off the outer half. Young at long off moves to his left and takes it. Another classy innings by Agarwal. Kiwis will hope this opens the floodgates.
Howout: c Will Young b Ajaz Patel

Commentary: All of a sudden something is happening now. This lands on leg and turns away sharply. Pujara looks to flick, it goes off a soft leading edge on the off side.
On middle, kept out nicely.
A single now as this is pushed wide of long off.
An apples but turned down. This lands outside leg. It holds its line. Full leaves it alone. It hits the glove and the pad as Gill tries to pad it away.
A bumper, ducked under.
On off, Pujara pushes it to mid off.
Shorter and on the body, this is worked on the leg side for one.
Bangs it short and on the body. Gill looks to pull but misses to get hit on the body.
One more short ball on the body, Gill ducks.
Yet another short one, Gill pulls it down to fine leg for one.
Around off, Gill looks to block but gets an outside edge which doesn't carry to first slip.
A touch short and wide, turning away. Gill reaches out and slaps it towards point where Somerville makes a good stiop. Single taken.
Tossed up, on off. Pujara skips down the track and pushes it through the cover region for a couple.

What happened here! Shorter in length, around middle and turning away. Pujara rocks back, looking to pull but the ball holds a bit in the surface. Pujara is halfway through his shot as the ball goes off the toe end towards slip.
On off and kept out.

NOT OUT! What a fantastic review from Cheteshwar Pujara! This is looked out from the naked eye but Pujara survives. Tossed up, on off and turning away slightly. Pujara strides out to defend but gets rapped on the pads. Ajaz Patel appeals and the umpire raises his finger. The review is taken and UltraEdge confirms that there's no bat involved. Ball Tracker shows that it's pitching in line, the impact is in line but it was just spinning enough to miss the off stump.
A length ball, down the leg side. Gill shuffles across a bit looking to pull but the ball goes off the thigh pads and into the keeper's mitts.
LEG BYE! Well-directed short ball, at the body. Gill manages to keep it down behind short leg, off the hips and picks up a leg bye.
Another bumper, around leg stump. Pujara ducks under it.
Shorter in length again, going over the middle stump. Pujara gets really low to let it through to the keeper.
On a length, around off and angling across. Pujara keeps it out towards short mid off.
Another short one to finish. This is on middle and goes over the off stump. Pujara yet again just ducks under it.
On a length, around middle and pushing the batter back. Gill dabs it down towards short leg.
On middle, eased down towards mid on for a single.
Drifted into the pads and then turning away. Pujara plays it with soft hands on the leg side.
Fuller one, on middle and pushed towards short mid-wicket.

OUT! TAKEN! Ajaz Patel with yet another wicket in this Test match. Nicely tossed up, on off stump and the ball grips and turns away. Cheteshwar Pujara presses forward looking to block it but ends up getting a slight feather on it. The ball goes towards first slip, where Ross Taylor takes a fine low catch. The umpires do go upstairs wanting to make sure it's a clean catch and after having a good look at it, the third umpire decides that the fingers were underneath the ball. Cheteshwar Pujara has to depart after a positive outing.
Howout: c Ross Taylor b Ajaz Patel

Commentary: On off, punched towards mid off.
FOUR! Short ball, around leg stump. Shubman Gill makes room and pulls it through mid-wicket and picks up a boundary.
A length ball, around off and angling away. Left alone by Gill.
Short again, this time Gill gets cramped for room as he manages to dab it down on the leg side.
Short again, down the leg side and guided down to fine leg for a single.
Good-length ball, around off and Kohli presses forward to defend it out.
On middle and leg, worked towards mid on.
On off, this is pushed down to long off for one.
On off, defended.
Outside off, this is played through point for one.
Loopy ball, extra bounce on this one. Defended.
NOT OUT! On off, this is pushed back to the bowler. Ajaz gets cheeky as he back flicks it onto the stumps at his end. An appeal and it is referred but replays show that Kohli is in.
Floated up on off, kept out.
Drifting down the leg side. Kohli looks to flick it but misses.
Another one drifting down the leg. Virat Kohli looks to work it away but it is way down the leg side.
Shorter length, on off. Kohli drops it towards the on side with soft hands.
On a length directing towards middle and leg. Kohli clips it to deep square leg for a single.
Short ball from 'round the wicket this time. Gill looks to pull it first but then keeps his bat there. The ball hits right at the top of his handle and goes behind square on the on side.
FOUR! Short ball outside off this time. Shubman Gill backs away and slaps it wide of the diving mid off fielder for a boundary.
Ohh...turn and bounce! Tossed up on off. Kohli looks to defend it but the ball beats the outside edge of his blade as it turns away.
Tossed up on off. Defended off the front foot.
Quicker on off. Blocked off the front foot.
Shorter length outside off this time. Kohli slaps it towards covers. The fielder there misfields and give away a single.
Tossed up on off. Defended off the front foot by Gill.
Shorter length and outside off. Gill cuts it to point.
On a length, on off. Kohli defends this off the front foot towards the off side.
On a length and angling into off. Kohli gets back and defends it.
A length ball, on middle. Worked towards deep square leg for a single.
Short ball from 'round the wicket. Gill pulls it to long leg for another single.
A length delivery on middle. Kohli blocks it off the front foot.
On a length and around off this time. Kohli pushes it off the front foot towards point.
Tossed up on middle. Gill skips down the track and pushes it back to the bowler.
Tossed up delivery again on middle. Pushed to covers this time.
Slower in the air on middle this time. Gill defends this off the front foot.
An arm ball this time. Gill gets back and punches it square on the off side.
Tossed up on off. Gill drives it to long off for a single.
On middle and Kohli turns it away to mid-wicket with his strong wrists. Rachin Ravindra does well there and keeps it to just a single.
Short ball on middle from 'round the wicket. Kohli pulls it well but straight to the square leg fielder.
Short ball again but down the leg side this time. Kohli leaves it alone.
Another short delivery around leg. Virat Kohli looks to pull this time but misses.
He connects the pull this time! Short ball again on off. Kohli pulls it to fine leg for a single.
Length ball, on the pads. Gill tucks it to square leg.
Shorter length again on middle. Gill just backs away a little and taps it towards the off side.
What a ball! Tossed up on leg, The ball turns away sharply and beats the outside edge of his blade. The ball hits his pads and goes towards the fielder.

NOT OUT! Tossed up again on off and this one seems to be going on with the arm. Virat Kohli looks to defend it but gets the inside edge of his blade onto the pads. There is an appeal for LBW. But the umpire says no. They take a review and replays roll in. UltraEdge shows huge spike off the blade and the decision stays not out.

TWO BYES! Ajaz Patel has bowled three absolute world class deliveries. Tossed up, around the off stump, allowing the ball to do its bit. The ball grips, bounces and turns away sharply. Virat Kohli is comprehensively beaten and the extra bounce deceives the keeper as well as it goes through him. The batters take a couple of byes and the ball goes towards third man.
Shorter length this time on middle. Virat Kohli uses his wrists and works it towards the deep mid-wicket region. Theey run three. Good running by the Indian batters.
On middle and leg, Worked towards the on side for a single.
Tossed up on middle. Kohli blocks it out.
On the pads and Gill tucks it to long leg for a single.
Short ball this time on leg. Virat Kohli decides to let it go.
On a length, on the pads. Kohli looks to tuck it away but gets rapped up on thigh. The ball deflects towards the on side.
On a length, on middle. Kohli works it to square leg.
Short ball on off this time. Kohli pulls it infront of square and gets a single towards the fielder at cow corner.
Shorter length again. Gill gets back and defends it comfortably.
Quicker through the air on middle. Kohli blocks it out.
Tossed up on middle. Kohli pushes it back to the bowler.
This is dragged down short but stays low. Kohli pulls it to square leg for a single.
Quicker again on off. Gill defends this out.
Quicker again outside off and turns away sharply. Gill decides to leave it alone.
Tossed up on off. Shubman Gill pushes it to the fielder at short extra cover. So India are 142/2 on Lunch on day 3 of this Test match.
Tossed up, on middle. Kohli nudges it towards short leg.
A touch fuller, around off and driven towards short mid off.
Very full, around middle. Kohli jams it out towards mid on.
On middle and leg, turning in. Kohli looks to turn it on the leg side but pads it just short of short leg.
On middle again and kept out on the leg side.
On a length, around off and turning in. VK goes on the back foot and works it towards square leg for a single.
Nicely bowled! Floated up, around off and this one turns away nicely. Virat Kohli presses forward to push at it but gets beaten on the outside edge.
On off and kept out on the off side.

That one just popped up off the surface! On a length, around off and the ball hits a crack and takes off as it spins away. Virat Kohli is take by surprise as he gets a thick edge towards short third man. They come back for two.
Around off, defended out.
Nicely bowled again! Tossed up, on off and allowing the ball to do the job. Kohli strides forward but gets another outside edge, past first slip. They take a single.
On off and punched down towards long off for a single.
Floated up, around off. Shubman Gill uses his feet to push it towards long on for one.
Looped up, on off and Kohli drives it off the inner half of the bat towards mid off.
Slightly shorter, outside off and turning in. VK gets right behind the line of the ball.
Fullish ball, on off and driven through mid on for a single.

SIX! Just over! Nicely tossed up, on off. Shubman Gill skips down the track and lifts it really high towards the cow corner fence. The fielders from deep mid-wicket and long on converge but can't get to it as the ball sails over the fence.
Slowed up and bowled on off stump. Gill keeps it out.
Flatter one, angled into middle and leg. Kohli pushes it out on the leg side for a run.
Fired in at leg stump. Gill jams it out on the off side.
On a nagging length, around middle and turning away. Gill goes on the back foot to defend.
Ravindra gives it a bit more air and bowls it on off stump. Gill watchfully keeps it out.
On the pads and nudged towards mid-wicket for one.
Tossed up, outside off and Kohli defends it towards cover.
On a length, outside off and turning in. Gill puts out a stride and pads it away on the off side.
FOUR! On off and Gill slogs it away with the turn and finds the mid-wicket fence.
Floated up, on middle. Shubman Gill uses his feet to ease it down to long on for a single.
SIX! All the way! Somerville tosses it up, outside off. Virat Kohli skips down the track and uses his wrists to slog it away, well over the mid-wicket fence for a biggie.
On middle, pushed down the ground for a single. It's pretty easy out there for the Indian batters at the moment.
Shouts of 'Catch it' but its well wide of short leg. On a length, around off and turning in. Gill strides out to defend but gets an inside edge onto the pads and just wide of short leg.
Dragged down, around off and pulled straight to mid on.
Pushed through, outside off. Kohli goes on the back foot and works it towards cover.
On middle and driven towards mid on.
A touch short and wide, cut away to cover.
Tossed up, around off and turning away a bit. Virat Kohli puts out a stride and leaves it alone.
On off, defended out. Maiden over from Rachin Ravindra.
Flighted ball, on off. Gill steps out and defends it back to the bowler.
FOUR! Shubman Gill gets a bit funky now. On a length, around off. Gill reverse sweeps it behind square on the off side for a boundary.
Flatter one, around middle and leg. Gill comes forward and nudges it past short leg.
Down the leg side, Gill paddles it fine and gets back for the second.
On middle, pushed towards mid on.
A tad bit shorter, around middle. Gill goes on the back foot and dabs it down towards backward square leg for a single.
Short and wide, played to deep point for a run.
Pushed through, around off and turning away. Kohli hops back and works it towards square leg for one.
NO BALL! On off, eased towards mid off. A no ball is called as Rachin Ravindra oversteps.
Around off, nudged towards cover-point for a quick single. The throw at the keeper's end is a bit wild and they do get an overthrow as well.
On off and kept out by Gill.
Quicker one, around off and defended out.
Fullish ball, on middle and leg. Gill works it with soft hands towards mid on and scampers through for a run. Good running.
Spilled down the leg side and spinning further away. Gill looks to paddle but misses and the keeper does well to pouch it.
Flatter one, on off and punched off the back foot on the off side for a run.
Flighted ball, on off and Kohli taps it towards short mid on.
Tossed up, around off and defended out.
On off, Kohli strides forward and works it past short mid on for a single.
On a length, on off and Gill defends it off the back foot.
Outsidr off, left alone.
On off, this is pushed to covers.
Slower and the line is just outside off, left alone.
Flatter and on middle, Gill hangs back and defends.
Well left! Just outside off, Gill does not fiddle with it.
On off, this is pushed to covers.
Kohli comes down the track, the length is shortened, it is worked to mid-wicket.
Slower through the air, outside off, Kohli looks to defend, this turns back in and goes off the inner half on the leg side.
On middle, this is worked through mid-wicket for one.
Loopy ball on middle, this is pushed to mid on.
Short and down the leg side, this is pulled to fine leg for one.
A single to end the over as Kohli plays this through covers.
Shorter and outside off, extra bounce on this one, Kohli looks to cut as he tries to get on top of the bounce but under edges it to covers.
Outside off, left alone.

Turn, bite, bounce. That had everything. Quicker and on middle, this turns away, skids through and there is also extra bounce. Kohli goes back and tries to defend. It goes off the outside edge to point.
FOUR! Up and over! This is way too short, Kohli rocks back and pulls it over mid-wicket for another boundary.
On middle, defended.
Another one on the stumps, kept out.
Tossed up outside off, defended.
Gill comes down the track, does not get to the pitch of it and hence, he looks to drag it, it goes just over mid-wicket for one.
On middle, this is worked through mid-wicket for no runs.
Flatter and on off, Kohli guides it to point for one.
Top edge but safe! The reverse sweep comes out. Due to the extra bounce in the surface, it goes off the top edge, lands safe and rolls towards third man for two.
On the pads, Gill looks to defend but misses to get hit on it.
Outside off. This stays low. Kohli is beaten as he tries to cut.
Shorter, this is pulled through mid-wicket for one.
On off, kept out.

OUT! TAKEN! Stop the press, finally, someone other than Ajaz Patel has taken a wicket for the Kiwis. Soft dismissal. This is short. Gill lines up to cut it but this one comes in with the angle. He then tries to push it but does so uppishly and straight into the hands of Tom Latham at covers.
Howout: c Tom Latham b Rachin Ravindra

Commentary: Iyer is off the mark as he works it through square leg.
On off, this is pushed to covers.
On middle, defended.
SIX! Into the stands. Solid use of the feet. Steps down the track and heaves it with the spin over mid-wicket. That was just the third ball Iyer faced. He's come out with intent.
SIX! Back-to-back biggies! The message is clear now, India are going for quick runs. Once again comes down the track, this is tossed up, Iyer whips it well over the mid-wicket fence for a maximum.
On middle, this is worked to mid-wicket.
Fuller and on middle, this is pushed down to long on for one.
Down the leg side. Kohli looks to sweep but mistimes it to short fine leg.
BIG TURN! This lands on off and then spins away. Iyer is beaten as he tries to block.

OUT! STUMPED! Iyer has nothing behind the crease and that is probably the right decision. Ajaz Patel strikes again. What a game this guy is having. What a beauty of a delivery. It is tossed up on middle, it lands and then turns away. Iyer lunges to defend but is beaten. The keeper whips the bails off and enquired in a polite manner. It is referred and replays show that Iyer is short. Another batter comes and another goes but no declaration.
Howout: st Tom Blundell b Ajaz Patel

Commentary: Saha is off the mark! On off, this is pushed through covers for one.
On middle, defended.
On the pads, this is worked through square leg for one.
FOUR! Swept and done so nicely! On middle, this is played through square leg. Boundary.

OUT! Dragged on! Virat Kohli is left in disbelief as he chops it on. Rachin Ravindra bowls it a bit short and wide, spinning away. Virat Kohli looks to cut it off the back foot but doesn't quite rock back into the correct position to play the shot. In the end, he is left fetching for it a bit and the ball comes off the bottom edge and goes on to hit the off stump. New Zealand get two quick wickets and they will be a bit relieved now.
Howout: b Rachin Ravindra

Commentary: Quicker one, on middle and spinning down the leg side. Patel leaves it alone.
Very full, on off and pushed towards mid off.
Flatter one, turning into the pads and dabbed down on the leg side.
Tossed up, on off and defended back to the bowler.
FOUR BYES! This one went through everyone. On middle and the ball spins in sharply off a foot mark and goes down the leg side, past the keeper and leg slip. The ball races away into the fence.
Fuller one, on off and kept out on the off side.
Loopy delivery, drifted into off stump. Saha paddles it behind square and picks up a couple.
Doesn't carry! On middle and truning away. Saha pushes at it with hands as the outside edge is found but it is short of the first slip fielder.
On middle, kept out.
Tossed up, around off. Wriddhiman Saha steps out and looks to go aerial on the leg side but gets a leading edge. Luckily for him, the ball goes just over cover-point and they take two.
On middle and leg, defended out.
Tossed up, on off and turning in. Patel nudges it towards short mid on.
A skidder, on middle and pushed towards short mid on.
Gives it a bit more air and bowls it on off. Patel watchfully keeps it out on the leg side.
On middle and leg, flicked away towards square leg for a single.
FOUR! Up and over! On middle, Saha gets down on one knee and swings against the turn. He gets a good connection and the ball ends up in the vacant mid-wicket fence.
Well bowled, On off and kept out by Saha.
Slowed up, on off and Patel plays it with soft hands back onto the deck.
Around off and this is driven through covers for a couple.
Flatter one, on off and pushed towards mid on.
SIX! High and handsome! Tossed up, on off. Axar Patel skips down the track and hits it with the spin as he clears the wide long on fence with ease. The lead is over 500 now.
On a length, around off and turning in. Patel dabs it down towards short leg.
On middle and defended out.
Around off and spinning away. Saha manages to keep it out off the back foot.

OUT! TAKEN! Rachin Ravindra gets his third wicket and Wriddhiman Saha has to depart. Saha went for one too many and paid the price. Tossed up, on a length, around middle and leg. With the ball turning away, Saha looks to lift it against the spin. The ball goes high and behind mid on. Kyle Jamieson back-paddles and takes a fine catch. Also, Jayant Yadav walks out to bat.
Howout: c Kyle Jamieson b Rachin Ravindra

Commentary: FOUR! Dragged down, on middle and spinning in. Axar Patel rocks back and pulls it powerfully past the short leg fielder and into the fence.
SIX! Huge-hit! Tossed up, outside off. Axar Patel skips down the track, gets to the pitch of the ball and smokes it with the spin. The ball sails way over the long on fence.
Quicker one, on off and angled in. Patel keeps it out off the back foot.
SIX! Another one! Full and wide, Patel whacks it over the long off fence for yet another maximum.
Floated up, on off and kept out by Yadav.
Beaten! Tossed up, around middle. This one turns and bounces. Yadav looks to block but gets beaten on the outside edge.
And again! On a length, around middle. Jayant Yadav goes on the back foot but gets beaten yet again.
Three in a row now! Flighted ball, on off and turning away sharply. Jayant Yadav is comprehensively beaten.
On middle, Yadav pushes at it and almost loops it back to the bowler.
On off and kept out by Yadav. End of a maiden over from Ajaz Patel.
Ravindra comes from 'round the wicket and bowls it quicker on off stump. The ball turns back in sharply but Patel keeps it out.
SIX! On a length, on middle and turning in. Axar Patel dances down the track but doesn't quite get to the pitch of the ball. Patel still keeps his shape and hits it over the mid-wicket fence.
FOUR! Short and wide, Patel waits for it and cuts it really late and fine. The ball goes quickly pst the first slip and runs away into the fence.
Quicker one, on leg stump. Patel fends it away.
On the pads and nudged towards mid-wicket for a quick single.
Slowed up, around off. Yadav plays it with soft hands towards gully.
FOUR! Hammered! Axar comes down the track and gets to the pitch of it. He smashes it down the ground to the long on fence.
The sweep comes out now, it goes more off the top edge towards deep square leg for one.
SIX! Yadav now joins the act! He skips down the track, does not quite get to the pitch of it but still clears long on for a biggie.
Flatter and on middle, Yadav hangs back and defends.
On middle, blocked.

OUT! CAUGHT AND BOWLED! Ajaz Patel gets his 14th wicket of the Test match and that's the best ever bowling performance by any bowler against India in Test matches. Take a bow! Drifted into middle and leg, spinning away. Jayant Yadav looks to turn it on the leg side but closes the face of the bat a bit too early. The ball goes off the leading edge and Ajaz Patel takes an easy return catch. Virat Kohli decides that it's time to declare. INDIA LEAD BY 539 RUNS!
Howout: c & b Ajaz Patel

Commentary: On middle, this is worked towards mid-wicket for one. New Zealand and Latham are underway.
FOUR! Young is off the mark in style! Down the leg side, Young flicks it, it races away to the fine leg fence.
Now angles this one on middle, Young blocks it onto the ground.
Yet another delivery, on the pads, Young flicks it through square leg for two.
Now an outswinger, shaping away from outside off. Left alone.
Another dot to end! Outside off, easy leave for Young.
On off, defended.
Floated up on middle, kept out again.
FOUR! Swept nicely! On middle, the sweep comes out, it is played through square leg for a boundary. Second of the chase.
Lovely ball and nicely taken! This is tossed up on off, this lands and spins away. Extra bounce too. Saha hops and takes it brilliantly after it beats the outside edge of Latham's bat.
Almost! On the pads, Latham looks to swee again, it hits his pad and then his hand, Latham falls over byt realizes the ball is rolling onto the stumps, he manages to push it away with his bat.
On middle, defended.
Angled into the pads, this is worked through square leg for one.
Back of a length and on off, Latham stands tall and defends.
On the pads, this is worked through square leg for one.
Back of a length and on off, defended.
Attacks the stumps yet again, blocked nicely.
A harmless nut to end, outside off, left alone.
On off and Latham keeps it out towards silly point.
This is slowed up, around the off pole. Latham strides forward to defend.
Slightly quicker, on off and Latham stays solid in defense.
Tossed up, on off. Latham pushes it out on the off side.
A bit of extra bounce on this occasion. Drifted into middle and leg, turns away after pitching. Latham looks to defend but the ball hits the splice of the bat.

OUT! LBW! Down goes the first wicket and Ravichandran Ashwin gives India the perfect start. This is nicely drifted into middle and leg and this one goes on with the angle a bit. The finger is raised. Tom Latham plays for the spin but misses and gets rapped on the pads. Latham does review it but UltraEdge shows there's no bat involved and Ball Tracker comes up with three reds. The Kiwi skipper departs early yet again and New Zealand right on the back foot now. NZ also lose a review.
Howout: lbw b Ravichandran Ashwin

Commentary: Siraj starts off with a bouncer, over middle and going down leg. Will Young ducks under it.
A length ball, wide of off stump. Young lets it through to the keeper.
Good-length ball, angled into off stump. Young gets right behind the line of the ball to block it.
Length again, outside off and shaping away a bit. Young shoulders arms.
Yet another harmless delivery outside off, not played at.

NOT OUT! Always looked like slanting down leg. Fuller delivery, attacking the pads and angling in. Will Young looks to flick it away but misses and gets rapped on the pads. The LBW shout is turned down but the review is taken. Ball Tracker confirms that it is missing leg stump and Young survives.
Mitchell comes down the track but yorks himself. It is jammed back to the bowler.
On off, this turns back in.Mitchell looks to defend, it hits the pad and lobs to short leg.
A single now as this is eased down to long on.
Flatter and on off, Young hangs back and blocks.
On off, this is pushed to covers.
On middle, defended.
Fiesty bouncer, angled right at the batter's helmet. Daryl Mitchell awkwardly sways away from it.
Fuller one, outside off and swinging in late. Daryl Mitchell makes an easy leave.
A length ball, again outside off and this one shapes away. Mitchell isn't interested in playing at that one.
On off and jagging back in. Mitchell stays solid in defense.
Another spicy bouncer at 141 kph, over middle and going down leg. Daryl Mitchell ducks under it well.
Full and a little wide, Mitchell pushes it back to the bowler off the inner half of the bat. A testing over ends in a maiden.
Bowled from wide of the crease and angled into middle but this one straightens. Young keeps it out.
FOUR! On middle and leg, Young looks to flick it away but gets it off the inside edge and beats backward square leg. The ball races away into the fence.
Around off, Young defends it off the front foot.
Tossed up, around off and turning in. Young keeps it down towards short leg.
Around middle, kept out on the leg side.
This one is pushed through quicker, on off. Will Young goes on the back foot and does well to keep it out.
FOUR! Lovely shot from Daryl Mitchell. Slanting on off, Mitchell punches it on the up and gets it through mid off for a boundary.
A length ball, on middle and leg. Mitchell keeps it down on the leg side.
Slightly fuller, skidding onto middle. Mitchell manages to block it out.
Another bouncer, going down the leg side. Mitchell ducks under it.
Good shot for no run. On off, Daryl Mitchell drives on the up and Siraj gets down low to his right to make a good stop.
Good-length ball, around off and dabbed down towards silly mid off.
Flighted ball, pushed wider. Will Young steps out but yorks himself.
On off and turning in, Young keeps it out on the leg side.
Tossed up, on a length, around middle. Young steps out and gets beaten in flight but manages to keep it out towards short mid-wicket.

What happened here! Shorter delivery, around off and turning in. Will Young tries to fend it off but the ball hits him on the pads, then pops up off the arm and takes a glove on the way as well. Wriddhiman Saha tries to guess where the ball is going but it falls down the leg side.
On off, kept out.
Tossed up, outside off. Young presses forward to defend.
On middle, defended.
FOUR! Thumped! Daryl Mitchell comes down the track, he gets to the pitch of the ball and hammers it down to the long on fence.
Flatter and on off, Mitchell lunges and defends.
On off, this is guided to point.
Slightly shorter and on off, this is pushed through covers for two.

Really well bowled! This is flatter, from wide of the crease, it is angled into middle, this lands and turns away. Mitchell looks to defend but it goes off the outside edge towards short third man for one.
A little too full and on off, this is jammed back to the bowler.
FOUR! Really good intent from Mitchell and good use of the feet too. Steps out and lofts it over mid on for a boundary.
Fuller and on middle, this is pushed down to long on for one.
BEATEN! This lands outside off, Young looks to defend inside the line, probably for the turn. This goes on with the arm and beats the outside edge.
Swept and swept hard but only for one! On middle, this is hit through mid-wicket.
On middle, this is worked to mid-wicket.
FOUR! Another excellent stroke! These two are using their feet really well. Young is quickly out, gets to the pitch of it and hits it over the bowler's head for a boundary.
Floats it up on off, Young defends.
Gives it air and lands it on off, Young keeps it out.
Flighted ball on off, Young defends it.
FOUR! Quicker but on the shorter side, this is pushed through covers for a boundary.
On off, blocked.
Fuller and on middle, this is pushed to mid on.
Outside off, this is pushed through covers for two.
On middle, defended.
Angles it into the stumps, kept out.
Floats it up on off, Mitchell lunges and keeps it out.
Another one on the stumps, defended.
Loopy ball on off, kept out.
Tossed up, around the off pole. Will Young keeps it out.

OUT! That is quite clearly off the glove! Kohli knew that and hence, he just reviewed it immediately. Young now walks back. That is a beauty of a delivery. Turn, bounce, just unplayable. This lands outside off, Young goes back to block, it turns back in sharply and also there is extra bounce. Goes off something to the fielder at short leg. The Indians are appealing, actually celebrating. The umpire shakes his head. Kohli reviews straightaway and it is a good review. India now 8 wickets away. Still 30 overs left in the day.
Howout: c sub Suryakumar Yadav b Ravichandran Ashwin

Commentary: FOUR BYES! Ashwin could have had two in two! What a beauty of a nut again. This is tossed up. It lands outside off and turns back in. Taylor looks to drive against the turn but it sneaks between the gap of bat and pad and goes over middle pole. The keeper does not collect it. Boundary.
Slows it up and bowls it outside off. Taylor looks to sweep but misses.
Outside off, this is pushed towards cover for one.
Sharp chance! On middle, defended to the left of short leg. Suryakumar Yadav gets his foot in the way and makes a good stop.
On a length, around off and cut away towards point.
FOUR! Close! Fired in at leg stump. Ross Taylor steps out of his crease but ends up yorking himself. The ball gets a faint inside edge and goes past the leg stump, into the fence.
Tossed up, on off. Taylor skips down the track and drives it towards mid off for a quick run.
On off and blocked out by Mitchell.
Slowed up, on off and turning away. Mitchell keeps it out on the off side.

OUT! TAKEN! Ross Taylor looked edgy out there and his brief stay at the crease has ended. Ravichandran Ashwin tosses it up, on off and turning in. Taylor gets low looking to slog it away. The ball goes off the top edge and is skied towards backward square leg. Cheteshwar Pujara runs behind from leg slip and takes a good diving catch. New Zealand reeling now with three back in the hut and Ashwin gets another one.
Howout: c Cheteshwar Pujara b Ravichandran Ashwin

Commentary: Beaten! Quicker one, around off and this one straightens. Mitchell looks to block but gets beaten on the outside edge.
On off, Mitchell presses forward and gets an inside edge on the leg side for one.
Quicker one, on middle and kept out.
On the pads, Henry Nicholls looks to flick it away but misses.
Slowed up, on middle and pushed back to the bowler.
On off and kept out on the off side.
On middle, Mitchell plays it towards mid on.
SIX! Excellent use of the feet from Daryl Mitchell. Tossed up, around off. Mitchell skips down the track and gets to the pitch of the ball and whacks it over the long on fence for a biggie.
Flatter one, on off and punched through mid off for a run.
Tossed up, on off. Henry Nicholls strides out to defend.
Quicker one, around off. Henry Nicholls strides out again to defend but gets rapped on the pads. A stifled appeal, not given, probably hitting outside the line of off stump.
Tossed up, on off and Mitchell stays solid in defense.
Fuller one, around off. Daryl Mitchell looks to reverse sweep but gets a bottom edge towards the slip cordon.
On middle and defended off the front foot.
Gives it a bit of air, on off. Daryl Mitchell presses forward to defend.
Flatter one, from 'round the wicket and outside off. Mitchell keeps it out.

NOT OUT! Good review from Daryl Mitchell in the end. On middle and leg, turning in. Mitchell strides out to defend but the ball goes off the inside edge onto the pads. The umpire raises his finger but Mitchell reviews it straightaway. UltraEdge confirms that there is a deflection and Ashwin will not get his fourth wicket yet.
Tossed up, on off. Henry Nicholls skips down the track and pushes it back to the bowler.
FOUR! Short and wide, punished! Henry Nicholls rocks back and thrashes it through cover-point for a boundary.
Tossed up, on middle. Henry Nicholls steps out yet again and drives it firmly back towards the bowler.
Slowed up and bowled outside off. Henry Nicholls presses for ward to defend.
Patel goes full and bowls it around off. Henry Nicholls squeezes it out on the off side.
Another short one, outside off. Henry Nicholls goes on the back foot but can't get it past backward point.
Tossed up outside off, it is pushed towards cover for one.
Floats it up on middle, defended.
Fuller and on off, the driven comes out. It goes down to long off for one.
Loopy ball on the pads, Mitchell looks to flick but misses to get hit on the pads.
On middle, this is worked to mid-wicket for one.
Gives it air and lands it on middle, defended.
Angled into the pads, this is worked through square leg for one.
EDGED AND OVER! FOUR! Outside off, Nicholls throws his bat at it, it flies off the outside edge over the slip cordon for a boundary.
Good length and on the stumps now, defended.
On the stumps again, it is defended.
Outside off, Nicholls leaves it alone.
Outside off, fuller, this is driven to covers.
Comes down the track does Mitchell, it is blocked.
Loopy ball on off, kept out.
Yet another floated up delivery on off, defended.
On off, this is pushed towards cover for one.
On off, defended.
On the pads, Nicholls sweeps, it goes off the inner half through backward square leg for two.
Down the leg side, the batter looks to flick but no connection.

NOT OUT! It is off the pad! Down the leg side, Mitchell looks to flick but misses. There is a sound as it passes the batter. Saha dives to his left and takes it. An appeal but turned down. Saha indicates he did not hear anything. Kohli takes a review but Ultra Edge shows it is not off the bat.
Another one on off, it is pushed to covers.
Angled into the pads, this is worked down to fine leg for one.
On off, Nicholls blocks.
BEATEN! Outside off, Nicholls leans and looks to defend.
Down the leg side, left alone.
Floats it up on off, Mitchell keeps it out.
Fires it on middle, Daryl Mitchell stands back and blocks.
On off, blocked.
Angled into middle, this is worked to mid-wicket.
Two more! On the pads, Mitchell nudges it trough mid-wicket for two.
A length ball, around off and driven firmly towards covers.
A well-directed bouncer, on off and angling at the helmet. Henry Nicholls sways away from it.
Back of a length, around off and angled at the body. Henry Nicholls taps it off the back foot to point.

On off and nipping back in sharply. Henry Nicholls falls over a bit as he looks to play the on drive and inside edges it onto the pads. The replay shows that there was no inside edge and the ball was crashing into middle and leg.
Length again, on off and nudged towards wide mid on for a quick single.
FOUR! Attempted short ball, on off and this one sits up nicely for the batter. Daryl Mitchell hangs back and pulls it aerially and the ball races away into the square leg fence.
Fuller one, on off and kept out by Nicholls.
Around middle and leg, nudged onto the leg side.
Tossed up, on off and Nicholls stays solid in defense.
Quicker one, flighted around off and turning away sharply. Henry Nicholls makes a good leave.
Flatter one, on off, worked towards cover.
Turn, bite and bounce. Tossed up, around off and turning away sharply. Nicholls leaves it alone and Saha makes a good take. Maiden over.
Attacking the pads as this one is angled in from off stump. Mitchell does well to keep it out.
A length ball, around off and coming back in. Mitchell keeps it out on the leg side.
Fullish ball, on middle. Daryl Mitchell gets squared up a bit but manages to fend it away.
Good-length ball, outside off and left alone.
Around the off pole and tailing back in. Daryl Mitchell defends it on the leg side.
LEG BYE! Slanting down leg, Mitchell looks to flick but misses. The ball goes off the pads towards short fine leg and they get a leg bye.
FOUR BYES! Wrong line from Jayant Yadav. On middle and turning way down the leg side. Daryl Mitchell looks to defend, but the ball deflects off the pads and goes into the fence. Given as byes though.
FOUR! Tossed up, around off. Daryl Mitchell attempts the reverse sweep and gets right on top of the bounce as he also finds the backward point fence. Good shot.
Slightly flatter, on off. Daryl Mitchell bunts it on the off side and scampers through for a quick single.
Tossed up, on off and defended out.

NO BALL! Flighted delivery, on middle. Henry Nicholls comes down the track but gets completely undone in flight. The ball turns away and it's a difficult one for the keeper to take. Wriddhiman Saha is unable to gather as the stumping chance goes begging. A no ball is called for overstepping and Saha will be a relived man.
On off and kept out.
FOUR! Dragged down, on middle. Henry Nicholls hops on the back foot and pulls it through mid-wicket for a boundary.
Fullish ball, on off and ahint of reverse on this occasion. Daryl Mitchell stays solid in defense.

FOUR! Edgy boundary! A length ball, outside off. Daryl Mitchell throws his hands at it and gets a thick edge which runs down into the third man fence. The fifty partnership comes up between these two as well.
FOUR! A fifty of the highest quality for Daryl Mitchell. Attempted slower one, down the leg side. Mitchell tickles it fine and picks up another boundary.
Good-length ball, outside off and left alone.
Another one slanting down the leg side. No need to play at that one.
Yadav ends with a good bouncer. It's over middle and going down leg. Daryl Mitchell ducks under it.
Tossed up on off. Henry Nicholls gets forward and defends it to the off side.
FOUR! New Zealand are getting boundaries at regular intervals now! Tossed up on off. Henry Nicholls gets on his knees and sweeps it to deep square leg for a boundary.
Quicker on off. Defended off the front foot.
Around off and turning away. Henry Nicholls lets it turn and taps it to point.
Fuller on off. Henry Nicholls defends this off the front foot and gets the inside half of his blade towards mid-wicket.
Slightly shorter on middle and turning away. Henry Nicholls blocks it comfortably off the back foot.
Shorter length on off and skids through. Daryl Mitchell pushes it to the off side and gets a quick single.
Fuller on middle and leg. Clipped to mid on.
Beautifully bowled! Tossed up on middle. Henry Nicholls presses forward to defend but the ball misses the outside edge of his blade as it turns away sharply.

Another play and a miss! Tossed up again nicely on middle and leg. Henry Nicholls tries to defend it off the front foot but the ball misses the blade by whisker. Ravichandran Ashwin is getting good purchase out there.

Beaten again! Three in a row! Loopy delivery on off. Henry Nicholls puts his bat down to block it but the ball misses the outside edge of his blade. Saha says it had hit the off pole, replays indicate nothing as the batter is covering the stumps.
Fuller on off. Henry Nicholls defends this off the front foot. End of an outstanding over by Ravichandran Ashwin.
Slower in the air on off. Defended off the front foot.
Shorter length and outside off this time. Pushed to deep cover for a single.
Fuller on middle. Clipped to deep square leg for another single.
Tossed up on off this time. Carefully blocked off the front foot.
Slightly quicker on off. Pushed to covers for a quick single.
FOUR! Henry Nicholls gets the final ball away for the boundary! On middle and off. Henry Nicholls gets on his knees and reverse-sweeps it towards third man fence for a boundary.
Tossed up on off. Daryl Mitchell nicely defends it off the front foot.
Quicker and flatter on off. Defended off the back foot.
Fuller this time. Safely defended by Daryl Mitchell.
On leg and turning into the batter. Daryl Mitchell leaves it alone.
Quicker this time on middle. Daryl Mitchell looks to defend but gets hit high on the pads.
Ravichandran Ashwin bowls this quicker and flatter outside off. Defended off the front foot towards the off side.
Quicker and on a shorter side by Axar Patel. Henry Nicholls pushes it to covers for a single.
SIX! A clean strike by Daryl Mitchell! Tossed up on off. Daryl Mitchell skips down the track and lifts this straight down the ground for a biggie.

OUT! CAUGHT! Daryl Mitchell is gone now! He tries to play the same shot like the previous one but miscues this time and pays the price! Slower in the air on off by Axar Patel. Daryl Mitchell skips down the track and tries to go downtown again. But miscues this time. He gets it off the bottom of his blade towards deep extra-cover fielder. Jayant Yadav in the deep there takes a fine catch and Daryl Mitchell, after playing a fine knock has to walk back.
Howout: c Jayant Yadav b Axar Patel

Commentary: On middle, Nicholls strides forward and defends it off the inner half of the bat.
Tossed up delivery, Henry Nicholls comes down the track and pushes it towards long on for one.
Around off, Tom Blundell presses forward and keeps it out on the off side.
Fuller on middle. Henry Nicholls sweeps but excellent fielding by Shreyas Iyer at square leg.
Quicker on off and turing away sharply. Henry Nicholls looks to defend but gets beaten by the turn.
Slower in the air on off. Henry Nicholls defends this off the front foot.
Quicker again and flatter on off. Defended off the back foot.
Fuller on off. Defended off the front foot.
Carrom ball this time and outside off. Henry Nicholls looks to push at it but misses.
Quicker on middle. Defended off the front foot towards the on side.
Shorter length on middle. Worked away to mid-wicket.
Quicker and flatter on middle. Tom Blundell gets well forward to defend it.
Tossed up on off. Defended off the front foot.

OUT! RUN OUT! Mix-up there in the middle and Tom Blundell pays the price! Tossed up on off. Tom Blundell drives it to mid off and sets off for a single. Henry Nicholls sents him back as there is no run there. Tom Blundell tries to go back but throw from the substitute fielder, Srikar Bharat is accurate and Wriddhiman Saha whips the bails off as Tom Blundell is short of his crease.One wicket brings two and New Zealand have lost half of their side now.
Howout: run out (sub Srikar Bharat / Wriddhiman Saha)

Commentary: Tossed up on off. Rachin Ravindra defends this off the front foot.
On middle. Henry Nicholls presses forward to defend but gets as inside edge onto his pads.
On middle and leg. Turned away to mid-wicket for a single.
Tossed up on on off. Defended off the front foot.
On off and turning away. Rachin Ravindra leaves it alone.
Nicely tossed up on middle again. Rachin Ravindra defends this off the front foot.
Fuller on off. Rachin Ravindra drives it to covers.
Drifted into middle and leg, kept out by Henry Nicholls.
FOUR! A touch short, on off and spinning away. Henry Nicholls rocks back and cuts it behind square for a boundary.
Flighted delivery, around the off stump and well left by Henry Nicholls.
Sharp turn and bounce. Around off again and Nicholls makes another good leave.
Quicker one, on middle and leg, pushed towards mid on.
Angled in at middle stump, Nicholls defends it off the back foot.
Tossed up, on middle and kept out by Ravindra.
Beaten! Slightly quicker, on a length and around leg. This one turns square and Ravindra is comprehensively beaten.
Attacking the stumps this time, Ravindra stays solid in defense.
Floated up, at the pads and nudged onto the leg side.
Around middle and leg, driven towards mid on.
Full and wide, Rachin Ravindra drives it firmly but straight to mid off. Maiden over from Ashwin.
Drifted in on leg stump and this one straightens. Henry Nicholls defends it out.
Around off and turning away, left alone.
On middle and leg, Nicholls strides forward to defend.

FOUR! Edged...but safe! Henry Nicholls has batted pretty well and maybe deserves a bit of luck. On a length, around off and turning away sharply. Nicholls looks to cut but the extra bounce makes him get it off the outside edge. The ball flies past first slip and ends up in the fence.
On middle, Nicholls presses forward to defend.
Around off, Nicholls stays solid in defense.
Flatter one, on off and turning in. Rachin Ravindra plays it off the back foot and dabs it down towards short leg.
On the pads, kept down towards leg slip.
On middle and leg, defended out on the leg side.
Floated up, full and on off. Rachin Ravindra squirts it out on the off side.

No shot offered but easily pitching outside leg. Quicker one, around leg stump and angled across. Rachin Ravindra strides out but doesn't offer a shot and gets rapped on the pads. The Indian players appeal but not given. The replay confirms that it was pitching well outside leg.
Fuller one, around off and edged down towards third man for a couple.
Tossed up, on off and kept out by Nicholls.
Flighted delivery, on middle. Nicholls puts out a big stride forward to defend.
Quicker one, around middle and leg. Nicholls fends it away.
A touch short and wide, played off the back foot towards point.
Floated up, full and around middle. Henry Nicholls defends it off the front foot.
Nicely tossed up, but well outside off. Easy leave for Henry Nicholls and its a maiden over.
Around off, Ravindra strides forward to defend.
Quicker one, on middle and Ravindra keeps it out on the leg side.
On off and played towards point.
On a length, around off and spinning in. Rachin Ravindra defends it off the back foot.
Around off again and Ravindra keeps it out with ease.
End of another maiden over. Slightly slower, on middle. Rachin Ravindra presses forward and defends it back to the bowler.
Floated it up, around middle. Henry Nicholls defends it off the front foot.
On middle, nudged onto the leg side.
On middle and leg, Nicholls presses forward and fends it away onto the leg side.

Peach! Ashwin drifts this one in, around off stump but the ball just grips and turns away sharply after pitching. Henry Nicholls looks to defend but the ball goes past the outside edge and Saha with a great take yet again.
Tossed up, on off. Nicholls presents the full face of the bat and plays it towards mid off.
Tossed up, on a driving length but well outside off. Henry Nicholls doesn't take the bait as he lets it through. The umpires call for Stumps. NEW ZEALAND END THE DAY ON 140/5!
Beaten straightaway! A perfect start from Jayant. He tosses it up and lands around off, Ravindra tries to defend but the ball spins away to beat the outside edge.
Fullish and around off, this time Rachin Ravindra is forward in defense and does well to block it away.
Another full ball, this time the line is around leg, Rachin helps it towards mid-wicket.
The line moves to outside off now, a loopy delivery, turning away, Rachin covers his stumps and shoulders arms.
Lands it full and around off, skidding in, Ravindra brings his bat in front in defense.
Quicker and around leg, turn and bounce again, Rachin gets back to block but it takes his thigh pad and drops near silly point.
Starts with a flighted delivery on off, Henry Nicholls stretches forward and defends it back.
Slower through the air, full and on middle, again Nicholls defends it by getting forward.
Slightly flat, full and around off, skidding in, Henry is forward as he blocks.
Beauty! Full and floated, around off, a tentative front-foot prod from Nicholls as he looks to defend but it spins past the blade.
And again. Spinning away from the batsman, Henry tries to defend but is beaten by the turn.
Fuller and on off, the batsman has just watchfully blocked this out.
Tossed up, around off Rachin Ravindra defends it by pressing forward.
FOUR! Put away. It's important to capitalize on poor deliveries and stay positive. Short and around off, Rachin Ravindra goes deep inside the crease and cracks it through covers for a boundary.
Flatter and around off, Rachin stays back and defends it late to the off side.

Shout for an lbw! The finger stays down. That looked very tight. Virat Kohli has a word with his bowler and keeper and decides against reviewing it. Loopy and full, landing around leg and curving away. Ravindra is squared up in defense and gets beaten by the turn. It hits him on the back leg, they appeal but the umpire disagrees. The replays find it to be the umpire's call.
Fuller and on off, defended off the front foot.
FOUR! Punished! Short and wide outside off, Rachin Ravindra pounces onto it and slaps it square of the wicket on the off side for another boundary in the over.
A touch short and around middle, Nicholls gets back and helps it in the gap at mid-wicket for a run.
Floated and around middle, Rachin is forward and defends it on the leg side.
Presses forward to a full ball around off and blocks it to the off side.
Fuller and on off, Ravindra drives off the front foot but finds the cover fielder.
Extra loop on this time but the line is outside leg, Ravindra nudges it towards square leg.
Slower one, full and around off, Rachin Ravindra deals with it comfortably from the back foot.
Short and outside off, Henry cuts it to sweeper cover and now there is a protection in the deep. Only a run.
Edged but safe! Full and around off, landing and breaking away, Rachin pushes inside the line with firm hands and gets a soft outside edge. Doesn't carry to the slip fielders.
The batsman has just blocked that from his crease.
Flighted and outside off, Rachin Ravindra watches it carefully before making a leave.
Appeal for an lbw, not given. Tossed up around middle, turning and bouncing a lot as Rachin is again squared up in defense. It pings him on the pads but the appeal is not entertained.
Beauty, unplayable. Jayant Yadav lands it close to off and the ball spins away sharply, Ravindra has a tame push inside the line and misses.
Floated, full and on middle, and dipping in, Henry Nicholls brings his bat down quickly in defense.
Fuller and around off, Henry defends it soundly off his front foot.
FOUR! The broom is out! Full and around middle, a bit too full, Henry Nicholls brings out the sweep shot and nails it to the deep square leg fence.
Loopy and around off, Henry Nicholls defends it by getting forward.
Fuller and outside off, left alone.
Gives it some extra air time and lands it full on middle, Henry Nicholls stretches forward and defends it safely.
Turning away from around off, Rachin Ravindra gets forward but then offers no shot as he pulls his bat away. He was looking to play inside the line initially.
Loopy and around off, drifting in and turning out, Rachin Ravindra looks to defend but is beaten by the away spin.

FOUR! Boundaries have come this morning. This was courtesy of some sloppy fielding by Mohammed Siraj. Fullish and around leg, Rachin Ravindra sweeps it towards backward square leg where Siraj doesn't account for spin and misses. It races behind.
FOUR! Down the leg side, skidding further down, Rachin Ravindra sweeps it down fine for a boundary at fine leg.

OUT! CAUGHT! Two boundaries and a wicket. After two loose deliveries, it's a fabulous ball served by Jayant Yadav. He gets the line right and dishes it around off, Rachin Ravindra tries to defend the trajectory but the ball spins away to take a healthy outside edge. Cheteshwar Pujara is alert at second slip and makes no mistake. India are 4 wickets away as a gritty little knock from Rachin Ravindra is over.
Howout: c Cheteshwar Pujara b Jayant Yadav

Commentary: Flatter and a touch shorter outside off, Kyle Jamieson punches it from the back foot to point. Slight fumble from Mohammed Siraj but no run conceded.
Plenty of away spin on this delivery as it lands outside off, Henry Nicholls is caught pushing and missing inside the line.
Fuller and around middle, this time Nicholls covers the spin and defends it to the off side.
Some extra air time to this delivery, full and outside off, it's left alone.
Fullish and close to off, Henry Nicholls stretches forward and defends it with firm hands to the off side.
Goodness me! Sharp turn and bounce from around off, too venomous. Nicholls is beaten on the outside edge and Saha also fails to gather it. They steal a bye.
Floated and around off, fuller in length, Jamieson tries to defend but it takes the inner half and sneaks past Mayank Agarwal at short leg.
Flatter and a touch shorter on off, Nicholls eases himself on the back foot and pushes it towards covers for one. It's called a no ball for overstepping.
Tossed up ball around off, turning down sharply, Kyle offers no shot and takes it on his pads.

OUT! LBW! Jayant Yadav comes up with a perfect off spinner, he lands it outside off and gets it to spin back sharply into the batsman. Kyle Jamieson is caught on the back foot as he tries to defend. He misses and is rapped on the back leg. They appeal and the finger has gone up. Kyle Jamieson is not convinced and opts for the DRS. The UltraEdge shows no wood while the Ball Tracker finds everything in line. Three reds. New Zealand have lost their seventh wicket.
Howout: lbw b Jayant Yadav

Commentary: Turning back in from around off, Southee has his bat close to the front pad in defense.

OUT! BOWLED! Jayant Yadav has three wickets. A nothing shot from Tim Southee. He thought to attack the bowler but perished. A pair for him. Yadav slows it up and delivers yet another off spinner, it lands and spins back in, Southee is down the track for a big heave across the line but misses. The ball brushes the flap of his back pad and deflects onto the stumps. Things unravelling rather too quickly for the Kiwis.
Howout: b Jayant Yadav

Commentary: Leans forward to a full ball around off and defends it towards short leg.
Sharp spin from outside off, William fails to defend and is pinged on the front pad. The impact appeared to be outside off this time. End of an exemplary over.
Loopy and on middle, Henry Nicholls gets back and nudges it towards square leg for a run.
Nicely tossed up, full and around off, William Somerville leans forward and across to defend and does so in front of short leg.
Slower through the air, full and around off, William Somerville gets forward and defends it back.
Goes on the back foot to a shortish ball and taps it down in front of short leg.
Flatter and shorter on off, William stands back and plays it down to point for a single.
'CATCH' is the shout! Perhaps, it lands short. Full and flighted outside off, Henry Nicholls aims for a booming drive but fails to connect well. It drops in front of the cover fielder.

OUT! CAUGHT! Cleanly done in the end. Jayant Yadav is having a happy Monday morning. His off spinners are doing the damage. He calmly delivers it close to off and the ball spins back in to take the inside half of William Somerville's defensive bat. The ball hurries to Mayank Agarwal at short leg who goes down low to take the catch. He fails in the first attempt but then gathers it cleanly in the second. The two umpires get together and refer it upstairs. The soft signal is out and it will remain out as the replays find that Mayank has done everything correct.
Howout: c Mayank Agarwal b Jayant Yadav

Commentary: Almost the 5th! Lands on off and then turns away. Patel is beaten.
Again! Tossed it up, fuller and on off, Patel looks to drive again but it turns and goes past the outside edge. Good take by Saha who whips the bails off quickly but Patel is in.
Flatter and on middle, defended.
Quicker this time and on off, Patel is solid in defense.
On off, kept out.
Angled into the pads, Nicholls looks to flick but misses to get hit on the pads.
Outside off, left alone.

OUT! STUMPED! There it is, there is the last wicket. INDIA WIN BY A MASSIVE 372-RUN MARGIN! Ashwin bags the last wicket. Floats it up. Nicholls comes down the track, he does not get to the pitch of the ball. Still goes for the big shot. He misses as the ball turns away. Saha collects and whips the bails off. Ashwin gets his 4th and India, along with the game, win the series too.
Howout: st Wriddhiman Saha b Ravichandran Ashwin
